Iria and Selene return to their roots with a captivating romantic fantasy.

Dani is a normal girl, or at least she was until a book swallowed her and took her to Albion, a new dimension ruled by a noble class that imposes their rules. Hidden behind fake smiles and midnight balls, this is a world where visitors like her are mere servants at their mercy. Marcus is the heir to the Abberlain family and the only one with the power to return Dani home. It is a gift that many envy and that many would like to control at any price. One wrong move and the life Marcus has built could come crashing down around him. When fate unites them, Dani and Marcus will shake Albion's hierarchy to the core, but...disrupting the pre-established order is dangerous."
